<item>
            <title>[LU-17260] remote hardlink creation shouldn&apos;t create multiple agent inodes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17260</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Creating hard links to a file on a remote MDT causes an agent inode to be allocated on the target MDT.  However, if multiple hard links are created on the target MDT for the same source inode, a new agent is allocated for each hard link.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be better to create only a single agent inode on the target MDT and use it for all of the hard links on that MDT.  That avoids consuming a large number of inodes on the same MDT when there are multiple hard links to a file (e.g. &quot;&lt;tt&gt;rsync --link-dest&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; backups).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
